items.title: Bharat Dynamics: Strong execution drives growth amid margin pressures
items.description: The company’s robust order book, growing export potential, and aggressive capacity expansion plans underpin its long-term growth trajectory

items.title: Entero Health acquires Aayu Chemist app, cloud platform MedCords to take on quick commerce rivals
items.description: Retail pharmacies in India are facing challenges from quick commerce players, which are reshaping consumer expectations with faster deliveries and digital-first experiences.

items.title: Eli Lilly launches popular weight loss drug Mounjaro in India to tackle obesity and diabetes
items.description: The drug has seen strong demand in the US and Europe, and its India launch is part of Lilly’s broader strategy to expand access to innovative treatments in emerging markets.

items.title: Apple, Samsung account for 94 percent of India’s smartphone exports
items.description: Tata Electronics was the fastest-growing manufacturer in 2024, with 107% YoY growth. iPhones 15 and 16 were the major volume contributors

items.title: Indian hospitals focus on other geographies as Bangladesh patient numbers decline
items.description: Hospital executives told Moneycontrol that there is a partial recovery in the number of medical visas issued to Bangladesh, even as they have stepped up targeted marketing and outreach efforts and introduced transparent packages to attract patients from other countries.

items.title: Bain Capital-Manappuram Finance deal likely to be announced soon
items.description: Bain to acquire approximately 22 percent stake from VP Nandakumar, Manappuram Finance’s founder and MD & CEO and come up with an open offer to increase stake to 42 percent
